The paper proposes a novel algorithm for eye movement classification, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research. The algorithm is based on Bayesian decision theory, which is a common approach in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the algorithm's performance on different datasets, which involves statistical analysis (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.AI).
